Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-hush] <dukeleto> if people want to say that using a KMC AC makes us "worthless",  it doesn't even make sense. We will be a KMD fork *and* asset chain. Hush will have total control to change what we want from KMD, and also benefit from all of KMD's work.  It will be so much better than our old situation of seeing things go into KMD that I want, and needing to do lots of manual merging/porting to bring the code over.

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-hush] <dukeleto> And I want to clarify, HUSH will be a fork of KMD, but we are not trying to compete with KMD. HUSH is focused on communications, where KMD's goal is really to be an ETH replacement. Making HUSH an AC is like having our research lab in the center of a bustling university of professors and students, instead of having our research lab in the middle of the nowhere, working alone.  It's the difference of camping next to the river so you can drink water whenever you want, instead of walking 10 miles each way for a sip of water.

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-hush] <dukeleto> Your private key will unlock your funds on the new chain, just like with BTCH. You own your private keys, we never know them nor do we want to.

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-hush] <dukeleto> Shielded zaddrs cannot be transported *precisely* because they are private!!! They are doing what they are supposed to do.

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-hush] <dukeleto> I would never have planned to remove support for Sprout like this, but with an inflation bug looming, this is our best course of action. The best laid plans of mice and men often go awry

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-hush] <dukeleto> All the data on the Hush v2 network is "secure" in the sense that it is encrypted, no one's privacy has been diminished.  That will continue even when it becomes "unsupported" when we upgrade to v3

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-hush] <dukeleto> but the financial value of sprout zaddr funds will become 0/unknown, because they are susceptible to having evil people print as much money in zaddrs as they want. Locking all sprout zaddr funds after block 500,000 closes the hole, so an attacker cannot transfer those funds to the new chain
